# Appendix B: Evaluation Checklist (Quick Pass)

Use this for rapid first-pass evaluation. Answer Yes/No for each:

- [ ] Can I immediately tell what this screen is for?
- [ ] Can I see the current status/state of the record?
- [ ] Do I know who owns this record?
- [ ] Can I see what action I should take next?
- [ ] Is the primary action button clearly distinguished?
- [ ] Are destructive actions visually separated and guarded?
- [ ] Is the most important information visible without scrolling?
- [ ] Are labels clear and domain-appropriate?
- [ ] Are required fields marked?
- [ ] Do error messages explain what to do?
- [ ] Can I navigate back without losing context?
- [ ] Can I sort and filter data tables?
- [ ] Does the UI show loading states vs empty states clearly?
- [ ] Is feedback shown after every action?
- [ ] Can I access help without leaving the screen?
- [ ] Is keyboard navigation supported?
- [ ] Are automated decisions explained?
- [ ] Is there an audit trail visible?
- [ ] Is the layout consistent with other screens in the app?
- [ ] Can I tell at a glance if items are overdue or urgent?
